 CHAIRMAN of the National Union of Local Government Employees (NULGE) in Adamawa State, Alhaji Hammanjulde Gatugel, has been freed by the gunmen who abducted him on Saturday. The NULGE chair who was abducted from his residence in Mayo-Belwa, headquarters of the Mayo-Belwa Local Government Area, was freed almost the same time on Sunday. No one could say how much might have been paid as ransom before he was freed. Police spokesman DSP Suleiman Nguroje, who confirmed the development, said police secured his release. 